Description: Fix CVE-2026-41731 — require exact package match for trusted header types
 The trusted-package check in DefaultKafkaHeaderMapper used a prefix
 match (`packageName.startsWith(trustedPackage + ".")`) in addition to an
 exact equality check, which meant every subpackage of a trusted entry
 was implicitly trusted. Combined with Jackson's default bean
 deserialization, a malicious producer could send crafted header values
 that caused the consumer to deserialize arbitrary JDK types whose
 constructors carry side effects (e.g. java.util.logging.FileHandler,
 java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool) — a CWE-502 untrusted-deserialization
 flaw with potential RCE.
 .
 This patch drops the `startsWith` clause so trust is granted only on
 exact package match. Subpackages must now be added explicitly via
 addTrustedPackages(...). The `"*"` wildcard behaviour is unchanged.
 .
 Backport of upstream 3.3.x commit bd3cca108d88efd8e669f91b6628198359072472
 (origin commit 9439fbb9ec9f3ccdca205cf0bda446a4afa57531 on main) to
 spring-kafka 3.2.4. JsonKafkaHeaderMapper hunks from the upstream commit
 are dropped (the class does not exist in 3.2.x); test-file hunks are
 dropped (the source jar has no src/test tree). The Javadoc hunk and the
 one-line runtime fix are retained.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-kafka/commit/bd3cca108d88efd8e669f91b6628198359072472
Bug: https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-kafka/issues/4496
Last-Update: 2026-06-29

--- a/spring-kafka/src/main/java/org/springframework/kafka/support/DefaultKafkaHeaderMapper.java
+++ b/spring-kafka/src/main/java/org/springframework/kafka/support/DefaultKafkaHeaderMapper.java
@@ -224,7 +224,12 @@ public class DefaultKafkaHeaderMapper extends AbstractKafkaHeaderMapper {
 
 	/**
 	 * Add packages to the trusted packages list used
-	 * when constructing objects from JSON.
+	 * when constructing objects from JSON. Trust is by
+	 * exact package match; a class is trusted only if
+	 * its declaring package appears in this list.
+	 * Subpackages are not trusted transitively, but add
+	 * them explicitly if needed.
+	 * <p>
 	 * By default, the following packages are trusted:
 	 * <ul>
 	 *	<li>java.lang</li>
@@ -413,7 +418,7 @@ public class DefaultKafkaHeaderMapper extends AbstractKafkaHeaderMapper {
 			}
 			String packageName = type.substring(0, lastDot);
 			for (String trustedPackage : this.trustedPackages) {
-				if (packageName.equals(trustedPackage) || packageName.startsWith(trustedPackage + ".")) {
+								if (packageName.equals(trustedPackage)) {
					return true;
				}
			}

Description: Fix CVE-2026-41726 — stop caching failed selector lookups in DelegatingDeserializer
 When trySerdes() failed to resolve a serialization-selector header, it cached
 the selector string in the unbounded delegates map as a ByteArrayDeserializer
 fallback. A malicious producer sending records with unique invalid selector
 values could grow the map without bound for the life of the consumer,
 causing GC thrash and OutOfMemoryError (CWE-400).
 .
 This patch stops caching failed lookups and returns null instead, and adds
 IllegalArgumentException to the catch clause so selectors naming real but
 unsupported classes fall back to raw input instead of stalling the consumer.
 .
 Backport of upstream commit ca2337ba789c5778a10197bda17a62915247ff6c
 (GH-4489) to spring-kafka 3.2.4. Test-file hunks from the upstream commit
 are dropped (tests are skipped in the build).
